4 Section 51.1. A. There is hereby created within the Department
5 of Public Safety, the Office of Homeland Security. The Commissioner
6 of Public Safety shall be the Homeland Security Advisor and shall
7 possess or obtain federally recognized clearances as appropriate to
8 perform the duties of the position. The Commissioner of Public
9 Safety, as Homeland Security Advisor, shall be responsible for the
10 operation and administration of the Office. The Commissioner shall
11 appoint subordinates and employees and may make such expenditures
12 with appropriated funds, or from such other available funds as may
13 be necessary to carry out the purposes of the Oklahoma Homeland
14 Security Act and other programs specified by law.
15 B. The Commissioner may commission any employees appointed to
16 the Office as peace officers. Any member of the Office who receives
17 a commission pursuant to the provisions of this subsection shall
18 exercise the powers and authority of an officer of the Department of
19 Public Safety, as provided for in Section 2-117 of Title 47 of the
20 Oklahoma Statutes, provided such commissions shall be subject to all
21 requirements set forth by the Commissioner, and the Commissioner may
22 set forth any limitations on the power and scope of the commission.
23 All commissioned staff must obtain and maintain certification as
